{
  "texts": [
    "According to the results presented in Fig. 24, the bandpass filter is the most frequently (N = 72, 26%) applied technique to raw EEG signals to eliminate the lower and higher frequencies.",
    "A small number of articles implemented the high and low pass filter, respectively 12% (N = 33), and 11% (N = 30).",
    "Furthermore, few studies mentioned the Butterworth (N = 19, 7%), Notch (N = 17, 6%), Independent Component Analysis (N = 3, 1%) or some other (N = 21, 8%) filtering techniques such as Savitzky-Golay filter, Kalman filter, Elliptic filter and Chebyshev Infinite Impulse Response (IIR) filter.",
    "On the other hand, it is observed that 29% (N = 81) of the studies did not report any filtering technique.",
    "NormalizationThe studies are examined according to the normalization methods implemented."
  ]
}